premise_source_doc_sentence: Commodification of the womb is the process by which services performed by the female womb are offered for sale and purchased on the market .

In traditional Shingon halls , the Womb Realm Mandala is hung on the east wall , symbolizing the young stage of Mahﾄ」airocana.In this setting , the Diamond Realm Mandala is hung on the west wall symbolizing the final realization of Mahﾄ」airocana .
The Womb Realm is a very popular subject for mandalas , and along with the Diamond Realm  (  vajradhﾄ》u  )  Mandala forms the Mandala of the Two Realms .

The name of the mandala derives from chapter 2 of the sutra , where it is said that the buddha Mahﾄ」airocana revealed the mandala 's secret teachings to his disciple Vajrasattva from his `` womb of compassion '' .
